subSubSection.paragraph:
Size .—The largest specimen from the Pacific coast of Panama is a male from Isla Perico with CL 9.7 mm , TL 24.8 mm . The CL of the Gulf of California specimens ranged from 4.4 to 8.0 mm, and TL from 17.0 to 21.6 mm (
Villalobos 2000
).

Ecology .—Intertidal to about 6 m (
Wicksten 1983
); in crevices of rocks and under coral rubble on sand or mixed sand-coral bottoms.

